  "texts": [
    "The confusion matrices for the two evaluations are presented separately in Figures 2A, B.",
    "The second evaluation of GPT-4 (GPT-4 2nd) generally outperformed the first time (GPT-4 1st) across the metrics, particularly in the identification of TA (Table 2).",
    "The accuracy for TA reached 0.75 with a sensitivity of 0.70.",
    "The overall performance of GPT-4 in polyp classification has improved due to its update between the two tests.",
    "However, both models demonstrated limitations in accurately distinguishing between SSA and HP, which exhibit high morphological similarity, particularly in their early stages."
